-- Saudi Rabigh Refining Resumes Full Operations at Plants After Power Outage
-- B y   M a h e r   C h m a y t e l l i
-- 2010-10-25T06:10:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/saudi-rabigh-refining-resumes-full-operations-at-plants-after-power-outage.html
Rabigh Refining & Petrochemical Co.
said its refining plants resumed full operations today and
petrochemical production plants are being lined-up for start-up
operations, according to a company statement on the Saudi bourse
website.  The company, a joint venture between state-owned Saudi
Aramco and Sumitomo Chemical Co. of Japan, yesterday said its
operations were affected by an interruption of power supply that
happened the day before.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maher Chmaytelli in Dubai at 
